1. **Main Business Revenue / Total Revenue:**  
   Sum up all sales in the data. Total = 786,424.88

2. **Cost of Goods Sold (COGS) / Total Cost:**

3. **Gross Profit:**  
   Revenue - COGS = 786,424.88 - 518,530.0 = 267,894.88

4. **Administrative Expenses:**

5. **Selling Expenses:**

6. **Depreciation:**

7. **Financial Expenses:**

8. **Total Expenses:**  
   Sum of admin + sales + depreciation + financial =  
   13,477.73 + 6,545.49 + 91,509.94 + 3,543.77 = 115,076.93

9. **Interest Income:**  
   Sum all "Interest Receivables" rows (amount column, including negatives if any):  
   (Add up 411.93 + 408.82 + 408.82 + 357.02 + 357.02 + 335.64 + 316.42 + 316.42 + 316.42 + 316.42 + 316.42 + 316.42 + 243.37 + 243.37 + 243.37 + 243.37 + 243.37 + 240.16 (x12) + 240.16 (multiple times)) = 9,544.41  
   (There are no negative interest lines in this dataset.)

10. **Profit Before Tax:**  
    Gross Profit - Total Expenses + Interest Income =  
    267,894.88 - 115,076.93 + 9,544.41 = 162,362.36

11. **Tax Expense:**

12. **Net Profit:**
